<br>
Walkthrough is mostly correct, but a few differences.<br>
<br>
Soul Leech is dropped by Dread, Fright and Terror in Fear.<br>
<br>
The live Lhranc no longer spawns wielding Innoruuk's Curse.  When you hand the undead Lhranc the Sword, Will, Head and Heart, you recieve a coin.  Once you kill Lhranc, Marl will spawn right outside of where you found Lhranc.  Handing him the coin will get you Innoruuk's Curse.  Because Lhranc no longer wields IC, he quads instead of doubles, making the final step significantly more difficult than before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ureiaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reiaku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/15/01 10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shadowknight...</span><hr size=1> Lharnc is a pain in the ass, for every time he lands a hit, you take 500 damage<br>
